The 2019 FinTech Conference will take place on 11 September 2019 at The Venue in Melrose Arch with speakers from Discovery Bank, Tymebank, FNB and Vodacom. These speakers will cover a range of fintech topics, including digital banking, mobile banking, mobile payments, cryptocurrency, blockchain, AI and machine learning. The emcee for the event is The Money Show’s Bruce Whitfield, who will be joined on stage by: Tauriq Keraan – Tymebank CEO
Chris Williamson – Vodacom Group’s managing executive for M-Pesa
Lorien Gamaroff – Bankymoon founder and cryptocurrency expert
Christoph Nieuwoudt – FNB CEO for consumer
John Holdsworth – Tautona AI founder and CEO
Akash Dowra – Discovery Bank’s head of technical marketing and client insights BusinessTech editor Gareth Vorster said the conference will provide delegates with better insight into the local fintech industry and the latest innovations in this burgeoning sector. Register now Standard tickets for the conference have been sold out, but BusinessTech has made an additional 20 tickets available for late registrations. For more information, and to register, visit: 2019 FinTech Conference Website Please note that the additional tickets will only be available for a week, and will be allocated on a first-come-first-served basis.